Paused(address).details: Emitted when the pause is triggered by `account`.

Unpaused(address).details: Emitted when the pause is lifted by `account`.

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

paused().details: Returns true if the contract is paused, and false otherwise.

payInvoiceERC20(address,address,uint8,ui.details: Uses modifier IsNotPaid, nonReentrant and whenNotPaused.The parameter _dueDate needs to be inserted in number of days (uint8).The parameter _amount needs be inserted in wei. Double check the decimal input for each token.

params._amount: The _asset amount in wei (10 USDC = 10**6 for example). Double check the number of decimals for each ERC20 token before paying the invoice.
params._asset: Make sure the ERC20 token (base currency, USDC for example) is supported by Compound Finance V3. Using unsupported assets will result in an error.
params._cometAddress: The address of the Comet contract you want to call. Check https://docs.compound.finance/#networks to get the correct contract address.
params._dueDate: The due date of the payment, or invoice, in days.

payInvoiceERC20WithFee(address,address,a.details: Uses modifier IsNotPaid, nonReentrant and whenNotPaused.The parameter _dueDate needs to be inserted in number of days (uint8).The parameters _amount and _feeAmount need be inserted in wei. Double check the decimal input for each token.

params._amount: The _asset amount in wei (10 USDC = 10**6 for example). Double check the number of decimals for each ERC20 token before paying the invoice.
params._asset: Make sure the ERC20 token (base currency, USDC for example) is supported by Compound Finance V3. Using unsupported assets will result in an error.
params._cometAddress: The address of the Comet contract you want to call. Check https://docs.compound.finance/#networks to get the correct contract address.
params._dueDate: The due date of the payment, or invoice, in days
params._feeAddress: When using an additional fee, this is the address that will receive the feeAmount. Requires msg.sender address when param _feeAmount == 0.
params._feeAmount: The total _asset fee amount in wei.

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions anymore. Can only be called by the current owner. NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby removing any functionality that is only available to the owner.

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.

params._dueDateUpdated: Input the due date in Epoch time.

devdoc.title: Paytr

allowedCometInfo(address).notice: allowedCometAddresses keeps track of the allowed Comet addresses for Compound Finance + the number of decimals, to make sure no malicious Comet contracts can be used while making a payment.

allowedRequestNetworkFeeAddresses(addres.notice: allowedRequestNetworkFeeAddresses makes sure ERC20 payments originating from the Request Network protocol go through the correct ERC20FeeProxy contract. This makes sure Request Network can detect the payment. See function payOutERC20Invoice in this contract for more details.

payInvoiceERC20(address,address,uint8,ui.notice: Make a payment using an ERC20 token.This function can't be used while it's paused.

payInvoiceERC20WithFee(address,address,a.notice: Make a payment using an ERC20 token.This function can't be used while it's paused.

payOutERC20Invoice((uint256,uint256,uint.notice: Allows the contract to pay payee (principal amount), payer (interest amount) and fee receiver (fee amount). This function cannot be paused.

paymentMapping(bytes).notice: paymentMapping keeps track of the paid invoices. The mapping uses keyType string (the payment reference of the invoice)  and valueType struct InvoiceERC20.

updateDueDate(bytes,uint256).notice: This function allows the payer to update the due date of the payment. This is only possible when the initial payment had a '0' dueDate, for example when using the Paytr contract for escrow or crowdfunding. Updating the due date means releasing the funds.

userdoc.notice: Paytr allows you to receive yield by making early payments.
